    <p>Kopi & Song We­bisode: Jonathan Charles Tay</p>
    <p>This we­bisode fea­tures one of the co-founders of The Opera Peo­ple, tenor Jonathan Charles Tay. He will per­form pop­u­lar and less known songs by Aus­trian com­poser Franz Schu­bert. He will also chat about his ca­reer in Sin­ga­pore, fa­ther­hood and if he can still rock out to Jon Bon Jovi, front­man of Amer­i­can rock band Bon Jovi. View­ers can send in ques­tions dur­ing the live stream. Kopi & Song, a se­ries of mini-recitals and chats pre­sented by The Opera Peo­ple and fea­tur­ing some of the best lo­cal singers, aims to keep mu­sic-mak­ing alive dur­ing the pan­demic. The se­ries is sup­ported by the Na­tional Arts Coun­cil’s Dig­i­tal Pre­sen­ta­tion Grant.</p>
    <p>View it on www.face­book.com/TheOper­aPeo­ple/posts</p>
    <p>To­mor­row, 5pm</p>
    <p>Free</p>
    <p>Ro­tary In­ter­na­tional 3310 Vir­tual Con­cert For Covid-19 Re­lief</p>
    <p>The Ro­tary Club of Queen­stown Sin­ga­pore hosts this live-streamed con­cert, sup­ported by 72 Ro­tary Clubs across Sin­ga­pore, Malaysia and Brunei. Head­lin­ing the con­cert is Alexan­der Soup­tel, ac­claimed vi­o­lin­ist and ex-con­cert­mas­ter of Sin­ga­pore Sym­phony Orches­tra, and Masako Suzuki White, an ac­com­plished vi­o­lin­ist and prin­ci­pal of Vir­tu­osi Mu­sic Cen­tre. Other acts in­clude in­die post-psych rock band Bak­ers In Space and 17-year-old clas­si­cal opera singer Corey Koh.</p>
    <p>Watch it on www.ro­tary­dis­trict3310.org.my/ vir­tu­al­con­cert To­day, 7.30pm Free</p>
    <p>www.face­book.com/ro­taryqueen­stownsin­ga­pore</p>
    <p>SCO’s #DabaoSCO Se­ries: Un­par­al­leled Charm Con­cert</p>
    <p>This con­cert, led by Sin­ga­pore Chi­nese Orches­tra’s (SCO) res­i­dent con­duc­tor Quek Ling Kiong, was per­formed in March last year at the orches­tra’s con­cert hall. Duan Aiai, an erhu soloist of the Shang­hai Con­ser­va­tory of Mu­sic, played erhu con­certo Lim­it­less by SCO’s Wang Yun­fei. And SCO’s dizi mu­si­cian Lim Sin Yeo pre­miered a new work by Si­mon Kong Su Leong.</p>
    <p>Watch it on bit.ly/2B12Lh0</p>
    <p>Free www.sco.com.sg</p>


